  "style": "",
  "texts": [
    "Fine-tuning was performed on spaCy's pretrained transformer pipeline, with only the transformer and NER pipeline components enabled in the configuration file.",
    "All fine-tuning processes were run on a high-performance computing cluster at North Dakota State University's Center for Computationally Assisted Science and Technology, using AMD EPYC central processing units and NVIDIA graphics processing units.",
    "Preprocessing and tokenization were done using spaCy's built-in tokenizer; training runs were optimized with the Adam algorithm, with decay rates of 0.9 (beta1) and 0.999 (beta2) and a learning rate of 0.01.",
    "For each training run, spaCy was set to check NER classifications against the test set after every 200 iterations within an epoch, to generate language models at regular intervals during the training process, and to stop whenever additional training steps failed to improve the classification metrics.",
    "We then extracted the highest-scoring language model from each set, for a total of 2500 fine-tuned language models."
  ],
  "correct_citations": []
}